Eastern Cape premier Phumulo Masualle unveiled a life size bronze statue of antiapartheid leader and longestserving ANC president Oliver Tambo at his Mbizana hometown yesterday. The 1.7m statue cost R1.2million and was sculpted by the Koketso group, a company affiliated with Tambo s son, Dali.It is a second statue to be unveiled in the rural town as there already is another one at his Nkantolo village which was burnt at a heritage site two years ago.For the full story get a copy of the Dispatch or subscribe to our e-Edition for the complete newspaper with jobs, classifieds, crosswords, TV schedules and back editions